FitnessApp.ExDescription: Squats are a fundamental lower-body exercise that targets multiple muscle groups, providing several benefits.

Cardiovascular exercise, often referred to as cardio involves activities that elevate your heart rate and increase your breathing rate. Some common forms of cardio include running, cycling, swimming, and brisk walking.
Strength training, also known as resistance training or weightlifting, involves performing exercises designed to improve muscle strength, endurance, and size by using resistance.
Crunches are a popular abdominal exercise known for their effectiveness in strengthening the core muscles.
Mountain climbers are a dynamic bodyweight exercise that engages multiple muscle groups and provides several benefits.
Pushups are a fast and effective exercise for building strength. They can be done from virtually anywhere and don’t require any equipment.

By performing burpee push-ups as part of your high-intensity interval training (HIIT), you can increase your heart rate and improve your cardio endurance. 2. Burpee push-ups are a full-body workout. With proper form, the burpee push-up can activate your glutes, triceps, hamstrings, quads, and pectorals.
